A vintage travel poster style illustration depicting a stylized map of the Asia-Pacific region with Bangkok, Singapore, Melbourne, and Sydney marked by glowing golden pins connected by sweeping curved lines. The scene features iconic architectural silhouettes from each city rising from the map surface - Thai temples, Singapore's modern skyline, Sydney Opera House, and Melbourne's Victorian buildings. Warm sepia and amber tones dominate with pops of deep blue ocean. Paper texture overlay gives an aged, well-traveled appearance. Birds in flight arc across a gradient sunset sky. The composition suggests connection, learning journeys, and professional advancement across international destinations.
